summary: On Crowley’s side of things, seeing Aziraphale so entangled in his essentialist beliefs must be torture. He loves the angel, the...
body:
On Crowley’s side of things, seeing Aziraphale so entangled in his essentialist beliefs must be torture. He loves the angel, the angel loves him, but as long as Aziraphale hasn’t been able to free himself from this line of thinking, he would never do nor admit anything about it.
So, yes, maybe Crowley could have helped him getting rid off his beliefs a bit more actively ( 6000 years is a bit too long, even for immortal beings… ). But with that comes the risk of making the other one angry, or making him shut down completely. Challenging someone’s beliefs, even when these beliefs are obviously wrong and harmful, is a delicate and dangerous thing to do.
And Aziraphale is Crowley’s only friend. He is the only one that matters. Crowley couldn’t risk loosing this relationship.
Therefore, even if that means having a stagnating relationship for all eternity, Crowley is so terrified he might lose Aziraphale that he would never take the first step or challenge his beliefs too strongly.

summary: Aziraphale might be a bit awkward, but he's awkward in that "face it head on and soldier through even though everyone around you...
body:
Aziraphale might be a bit awkward, but he’s awkward in that “face it head on and soldier through even though everyone around you is getting secondhand embarrassment” sort of way.

Anthony J. Crowley, for all that he pretends to be smooth and suave, is “trip over a table and babble excuses to get out of telling your crush you like them” awkward and that is why Aziraphale is the one who decides that they’re dating.

summary: Mortal AU with a Greenhouse instead of the Garden of Eden UwU
question: Mortal AU with a Greenhouse instead of the Garden of Eden UwU
answer:
send me an au and i’ll give you 5+ headcanons about it

  • okay, so, it all starts with the “apple incident” which happened many years ago
  • which happened because one way too motivated teacher thought it a good idea to take a field trip with a bunch of teenagers
  • one of those teenagers: Anthony Crowley
  • now, every other reasonable teacher would go to a museum or the zoo or whatever it is where teachers go on field trips, but not this teacher. this teacher decided that the Eden Greenhouses by a famous gardener was the place to go. and for some weird reason they even got permission to visit it
  • so Crowley and his class go to the greenhouse, and Crowley has to pretent to be bored as hell even he actually loves plants but he’s trying to be a cool kid, so no one is allowed to know that
  • on the other hand, there’s Aziraphale, who’s not in Crowley’s class, but who’s having an internship at the greenhouse. he has no idea how he managed that. he isn’t even interested in that stuff.
  • anyways, at one point Crowley tries to prove himself to his friends, also it’s hellish hot in a greenhouse, and his clothes are sweaty and everyone’s in a bad mood, so he grabs an apple from his lunch and…
  • … does something. I have no idea what. But there’s chaos and a lot of shouting
  • and in the chaos, Crowley manages to get outside, where’s Aziraphale, minding his own business, because he doesn’t want to work in this greenhouse, and no one’s looking after him anyways, so he takes a lot of cigarette breaks. or maybe he just goes to the next starbucks and gets a muffin and some cocoa and just sits outsite, reads a books and drinks his cocoa, until someone notices him (no one ever does)
  • but then there comes Crowley fleeing the scene, and they talk for a bit
  • but someone finds them sitting there
  • and Crowley’s getting major bollocks from his teacher, and this isn’t the first time that Crowley pulled such a stunt, so Crowley’s parents decide that he should change schools, his friends are certainly a bad influence for him. Secretly Crowley’s glad for that
  • also Aziraphale gets fired because now people found out that he never really worked and just sat there and did his own thing. and he gets the shit from his parents for that too
  • but it’s okay because Aziraphale’s about to go to university soon, after all
  • and he gets an internship in a bookshop instead
  • also there are two dudes names Adam and Eve working at the greenhouse and they get fired that day
  • and many years later, Crowley and Aziraphale meet again by chance and they’re recognizing each other as “that dude from the greenhouse”
  • long story short, they fall in love

send me an au and i’ll give you 5+ headcanons about it

  • okay, so, it all starts with the “apple incident” which happened many years ago
  • which happened because one way too motivated teacher thought it a good idea to take a field trip with a bunch of teenagers
  • one of those teenagers: Anthony Crowley
  • now, every other reasonable teacher would go to a museum or the zoo or whatever it is where teachers go on field trips, but not this teacher. this teacher decided that the Eden Greenhouses by a famous gardener was the place to go. and for some weird reason they even got permission to visit it
  • so Crowley and his class go to the greenhouse, and Crowley has to pretent to be bored as hell even he actually loves plants but he’s trying to be a cool kid, so no one is allowed to know that
  • on the other hand, there’s Aziraphale, who’s not in Crowley’s class, but who’s having an internship at the greenhouse. he has no idea how he managed that. he isn’t even interested in that stuff.
  • anyways, at one point Crowley tries to prove himself to his friends, also it’s hellish hot in a greenhouse, and his clothes are sweaty and everyone’s in a bad mood, so he grabs an apple from his lunch and…
  • … does something. I have no idea what. But there’s chaos and a lot of shouting
  • and in the chaos, Crowley manages to get outside, where’s Aziraphale, minding his own business, because he doesn’t want to work in this greenhouse, and no one’s looking after him anyways, so he takes a lot of cigarette breaks. or maybe he just goes to the next starbucks and gets a muffin and some cocoa and just sits outsite, reads a books and drinks his cocoa, until someone notices him (no one ever does)
  • but then there comes Crowley fleeing the scene, and they talk for a bit
  • but someone finds them sitting there
  • and Crowley’s getting major bollocks from his teacher, and this isn’t the first time that Crowley pulled such a stunt, so Crowley’s parents decide that he should change schools, his friends are certainly a bad influence for him. Secretly Crowley’s glad for that
  • also Aziraphale gets fired because now people found out that he never really worked and just sat there and did his own thing. and he gets the shit from his parents for that too
  • but it’s okay because Aziraphale’s about to go to university soon, after all
  • and he gets an internship in a bookshop instead
  • also there are two dudes names Adam and Eve working at the greenhouse and they get fired that day
  • and many years later, Crowley and Aziraphale meet again by chance and they’re recognizing each other as “that dude from the greenhouse”
  • long story short, they fall in love

There was a certain look that Aziraphale wore occasionally—a pinched sort of moue that looked like he’d just taken a very large mouthful of cinnamon—which meant he thought Crowley was being ridiculous. He had put it on.

“Hang on,” he had said. “You want us to do human things?”

*

If you’re going to go native, you might as well go all the way.
